<p>Mediation is a component of the Wikipedia content-dispute resolution process. During mediation, a content dispute between two or more editors is subjected to the involvement of an uninvolved third party (who is the mediator). The role of the mediator is to guide discussion towards the formation of <a href="Wikipedia_Consensus" title="Wikipedia:Consensus">agreement</a> over the disputed elements of content.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
